nodes.bodyText:
A little off-topic, but how do these inline response classes get named?
Is there a chance of breakage if we add new endpoints with new inline responses or is the 2001 deterministic in some way?

I think swagger codegen names it based on the order of inline responses in the swagger.yaml.  I don't really see us adding new endpoints to the Quay API, but if we do, just add it to the bottom.  Even if we don't, it'll be obvious how to fix, compiler would complain and suggest what it should be.
